The outcome of the discussion would be objective. People should be protected from being slandered by historic and legal material used by political parties to damage the reputation of its opponent. The use of ambiguous statements should be avoided.

Quasi monopolies in Suriname, the electric service Suralco, Surinamese Airways, the telephone company and the Postal and Telecommunication Service should receive attention in the programme. In the past, these companies had adequate serviced to the people.

Government should be aware of imposing laws and regulations on former big companies that now have been nationalized are in conflict of interest.

Discussing the situation of politicians who have tried to damage the reputation of political opponents and are still continue to do so should form part of the programme.

Apartheid was an anti humanitarian policy and hence should not be discussed in Suriname. Discussing such matters with Afrikaners, who we can now see in Suriname will just hurt humanity.

The penalty of hanging is rediculous and represents the death penalty. (What is the death penalty?)

People aim to stay alive and not live a life of shame and disgrace.

People use money to get rid of nightmares.

There are other options, other than hanging. Examples are exile, being humiliated and castrated.
